## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

- Flappy bird map
- Home Screen
- Play button
- Base code for obstacle/map movement

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

- Flappy bird map
- Home Screen
- Play button
- Base code for obstacle/map movement
- Flappy bird movement with click
- Point tracker

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

- Flappy bird map
- Home Screen
- Play button
- final code for obstacle/map movement
- Flappy bird movement with click
- Point tracker
- High score tracker
- "Game Over" "Go to Home" "Play Again" button for loss
- Sounds that play for click animation, speed increase, and loss

## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?
I need to learn how to make a GUI using ASCII or other methods to make the different elemenets of the game such as the bird, obstacles, and map.
I also need to learn how to bind the users clicks to the birds movement and make it so hitting the obstacles results in a loss
instead of the bird just phasing through them. I also need to learn how to make the background move and make the speed change every five successful 
evasions. Most of the new skills I need to acquire are graphics and user input based. 
